OL,3,CYoung golfer aims to raise #100,000 in
OL,4,Cmemory of dad who died after transplant
OL,6,FGeorge is hoping to set a world record
OL,7,Fby playing five rounds of golf in five
OL,8,Fdifferent countries in twenty four
OL,9,Fhours. He will tee off in Ireland on
OL,10,FJune 20th and aims to finish the
OL,11,Ffollowing day in Wales. He will also
OL,12,Fplay on courses in Scotland, Ireland
OL,13,Fand in Cheshire in England.
OL,15,FHe'll be supported on the golf course
OL,16,Fby his grandfather Tony Sedgwick who
OL,17,Fsaid: "I feel like the luckiest
OL,18,Fgrandad in the world because I get to
OL,19,Fplay golf with George who loves the
OL,20,Fsport and plays in all weathers."
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G5/7
